July 29, 2017 12:25 AM ET
Banks

Company Overview of Shanghai Commercial Bank Limited



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Shanghai Commercial Bank Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides various retail and corporate banking products and services. The company offers various deposit services, such as current savings, checking, fixed deposit, call deposit, and student/children savings accounts, as well as payment services, currency exchange, safe deposit boxes, and ATM services; and RMB services, including deposits, cheques, exchange, remittance, and credit cards to individual and corporate clients. It also provides mortgages and loans, such as housing mortgages, government housing schemes, reverse mortgage, personal installment loans, personal tax loans, and shares overdraft facilities to individuals; a...
Shanghai Commercial Bank Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides various retail and corporate banking products and services. The company offers various deposit services, such as current savings, checking, fixed deposit, call deposit, and student/children savings accounts, as well as payment services, currency exchange, safe deposit boxes, and ATM services; and RMB services, including deposits, cheques, exchange, remittance, and credit cards to individual and corporate clients. It also provides mortgages and loans, such as housing mortgages, government housing schemes, reverse mortgage, personal installment loans, personal tax loans, and shares overdraft facilities to individuals; and financing services, such as term and installment loans, overdraft, trade finance, project finance, syndicated loans, etc., to enterprises. In addition, the company offers life, general, and commercial insurance products and services; remittance services; mandatory provident fund services; investment services, including investment funds, structured deposits, bond investments, physical gold trading, paper gold, and foreign exchange margin trading services; securities services consisting of stock trading and Internet/mobile stock trading services; debit cards; and Internet banking services. Further, it engages in the provision of nominee, trustee, commodities trading services, and I.T. application services; investment in exchange fund bills, insurance brokerage, and notes and bonds; and property holding and management activities. The company has 40 branches in Hong Kong; and overseas branches in New York, Los Angeles, San Francisco, and London, as well as in Mainland China. Shanghai Commercial Bank Limited was founded in 1950 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. Shanghai Commercial Bank Limited is a subsidiary of The Shanghai Commercial & Savings Bank, Ltd.
Detailed Description


Shanghai Commercial Bank Tower12 Queen's RoadCentral,  Hong KongFounded in 19501,770 Employees



www.shacombank.com.hk







