The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 29, 2017 12:25 AM ET
Banks

Company Overview of The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited



Snapshot People




Company Overview
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides a range of banking and related financial services in Hong Kong and rest of Asia-Pacific. It operates through Retail Banking and Wealth Management, Commercial Banking, Global Banking and Markets, and Global Banking segments. The company accepts current and savings accounts, time deposits, certificates of deposits, and other deposit accounts; offers personal loans, auto loans, overdrafts, and credit cards, as well as residential and commercial mortgages; and provides insurance, asset management, broking, wealth management, and investment and financial advisory services, as well as credit facilities ...
The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited, together with its subsidiaries, provides a range of banking and related financial services in Hong Kong and rest of Asia-Pacific. It operates through Retail Banking and Wealth Management, Commercial Banking, Global Banking and Markets, and Global Banking segments. The company accepts current and savings accounts, time deposits, certificates of deposits, and other deposit accounts; offers personal loans, auto loans, overdrafts, and credit cards, as well as residential and commercial mortgages; and provides insurance, asset management, broking, wealth management, and investment and financial advisory services, as well as credit facilities to customers for short and long term borrowing requirements. It also provides payment and transfer, foreign exchange, commercial cards, receivables finance, treasury and capital market, and import and export services, as well as commercial, industrial, and international trade services. In addition, the company offers business banking services for small and medium-sized enterprises, and corporate and mid-market companies; investment management and trustee solutions to high net worth individuals and their families; and tailored financial solutions to government, corporate, and institutional clients. The company was founded in 1865 and is headquartered in Central, Hong Kong. The Hongkong and Shanghai Banking Corporation Limited is a subsidiary of HSBC Asia Holdings B.V.
Detailed Description


HSBC Main Building1 Queen’s Road CentralCentral,  Hong KongFounded in 1865



Phone: 852 2822 1111

Fax: 852 2810 1112

